\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1468682\charrsid13856522 But - me father's brother used to come in - me Uncle To
m - and he had - he was like a Scotsman - he was, weekly payments - he used to get things for people and-on Saturday he used to come to Beswick and he was very much like me father in looks and a woman said to me mother one day, oh I seen - I seen - the ch
ildren with their dad spending their Saturdaypenny. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
She said, oh no you haven't. She said, you've seen their Uncle. But oh we loved him. And he went in the war and - when he came - the first time he came to see us when he was away for over three years the d
og nearly went through the window with joy - she remembered him. Me Uncle Tom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 How old were you when you first went to school?
