\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
No, we were too small. We were only babies really. My sister used to go to sleep and - when mother went down - we had little - we used to give little prizes, like texts. It - it was very religious. You know, we used to si
ng hymns. That's the - the principle thing I remember about it that when we got to school - there was a little harmonium and the teacher played it and we sang - sang hymns, yes. All things bright and beautiful. And Jesus - and Jesus bids us shine with a c
lear pure light, like a little candle burning in the night. Yes.
