gue - only, I can remember chiefly going up to Chaseley. Mrs Haywards house there you see and they used to bring out beakers of milk and buns and we used to play on the lawns and it - always seemed like summer somehow. Always - yes - except the time we we
re up when King Edward died and we walked in the scholars that year and we had to have black - sort of going that way - yes.
