\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
I really never considered it. I mean you - I suppose you'd call it the artisan class couldn't you. I mean me father was never a labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 What sort of people would you say belonged to the artisan class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well - I thinking person actu
ally I mean my father was very intelligent - I mean he could discuss politics and he was certainly very well read. He'd read every one of Dumas books and I'd read the lot when I was eleven. And we always had - and newspapers, I mean, even during the war w
e were - we had a children's newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 During the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Yes. But of course I think - years ago people were well read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Better than today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Much better. Now take for instance this - the Forsythe Saga. I go to houses - don't li
ke television. I don't like everything served up on a dish. And people talking and they're discussing the characters. Well if they'd read the book, they'd never make a hero of Soames - they couldn't possibly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 And you read this when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Years ago. Years ago. I mean all the serials - Vanity Fair - they're all feathery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You read those when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Can you ever remember being brought up to treat some people differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Were you ever told to show respect in some way to certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 We were just taught - to be well mannered. No matter who it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You didn't show special respect to the candidates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 No, not at all. Not at all. We - we had - we were found little jobs to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You don't remember calling anyone Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
No, if - if it was Mr Flanagan and he asked you you'd say yes or no, Mr Flanagan you see, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You don't remember calling anyone Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Do you ever remember anyone showing respect in this way to your parents?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Not really. I mean more or less say hello George, how are you? And call mother Marriet you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
In Beswick the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well I can'
t remember anybody outstanding. No - I mean - at - church it was - the Rector, Mr Crepney and the - there used to be people over the - the Sunday school teachers. We liked them, you know what I mean, they - sort of arranged things. Sometimes a ramble, we'
d go all over the north bit - north of the moons like on Saturday afternoon the Sunday school teachers would - pick them up, might be forty or fifty - and ask like do you want to join in a ramble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 So you don't remember anybody being considered more important than others?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
No, not really. I never - I never gave it a second thought really - they were just there. And it was living, you took it for granted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Who do you think the shopkeepers associated with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well take for instance the
 young man that keeps the shop next door - he went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Christchurch{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} like I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 When you were young who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Oh they didn't seem to be any different than we were. I went out with girls that their parents had shops but - I never thought they were any better than - only in some cases they had more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Who would you have thought the clergy associated with in your young days?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well they seemed to be all mixed up with the church affairs if you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 They mixed generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Yes. Like they used to have - little social events at - at church and people went, I mean sometimes it'd only be about tuppence or threepence and you'd get a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Who do you think the teachers mixed socially with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well none of them lived where - they always sort of - went away on the tram you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Do you remember any employers and who they mixed socially with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
No, not really. Well - as regards the teachers - I can't - I mean they - when you're young and
 they're - I mean teachers seem old to me - as I look back now I realize they weren't the old women I thought they were. But I mean when you're about eleven and - my mother seemed and old woman to me. They're just grown ups and you - you - it doesn't cros
s
 your mind, anything like that. I - I had friends - Welsh people they were. And - they went to a chapel on the other side of - it's pulled down now and - this girl worked with me but she just happened to live across on the other side. Now her - they were 
r
eally - musical. And when this girl got married we went to the wedding, they had a room at - a club room and her brother played the piano and - eventually he went to school of music 'cos I really think that Welsh people love music and now he's Richard Lew
is - the tenor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
But do you think there was a difference between people who went to church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
No, not - no, not - not really because there were several in our street that went to the chapel at the bottom of the road including Howard Thoma
s who's over - Independent Television. I - I played with him and his sister and they went to the chapel down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You don't think there was any social difference at all between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 No. Although Howard Thomas went - passed for the Grammar 
school and went to the Grammar school but we used to - I used to see him in the gods at the Princes and he was a great one for going to the theatre. 'Course there was no wireless or anything like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 In Beswick where you lived did all the pe
ople in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups amongst them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well there was a difference in this respect. Where there was a large family there was terrible poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 You saw this poverty did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well I can remember the teacher at school asking if any children had shoes because some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Can you remember any of them going bare foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
I can't - say that I saw any children barefoot - only boys in the park. And they - taken their s
hoes off - they'd taken all their clothes off because they used to go swimming in the stream. But the teacher used to ask - and it must have been done very discreetly because me mother used to ask at the club for - shoes and all that kind of thing and clo
thes that you'd grown out of. You'd take them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1468682\charrsid13856522 in parcels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
 - to school but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 This was the only difference in the working - classes that you observed?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Yes, I mean I went in a house where - this is rather funny - me father was in the Army and - the d
octor - our doctor garaged his car immediately opposite our front door and I'd been in this house and this woman had had several children. She had four or five, and I can see now the table was - she had the bed under the window and the table was pushed up
 and she was cooking the bread and of course the war was on and things were pretty bad and she cut the slices of bread -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 This was the 14/18 war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Yes. Cut the slices of bread and she put tinned milk on it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10097921\charrsid13856522  Goats}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522  milk. Goats milk in tins. And I re
member - she'd had this baby but it had been smothered - she'd laid on it - she was stone deaf. And I went and I said to the doctor as he put his car in - the next baby - you bring in our street, doctor Craig, will you bring it to our house because my mot
her won't lie on it. She isn't deaf. He told me mother. Father was in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Did you ever go into a poor house though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well that house - she had all these children and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Can you remember what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well that - don't you think
 that's poverty where - she - the kids are all round and I went home with this - we call it butty. Where've you got that from? Oh I got it from - Brooks. Well don't ever take any more. They can't afford to give butties away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Do you ever remember one group that felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well I mean I've heard remarks - oh they think they are somebody - but - it never occurred to me to wonder why they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Do you think some families were thought of as rough and some as respectable?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 
Well more or less it was perhaps somebody had got in trouble, you know, boys - the police had been or something like that but - in fact I remember when we lived at Eccles - at Lewis Street, a boy had the birch rod. And - everyone - at assembly this boy 
was brought out - he'd had the birch rod - whatever he'd done I don't know but that was the only case I ever knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Do you remember a distinction of any kind between craftsmen and labourers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13702913 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Well more or less a labourer's, they were poorer. I mea
n it was just that the - children were shabby. Didn't ever seem to have new clothes. Might have had - shoes that were too big for them all that kind of thing. That was the difference you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8198053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11950706\charrsid13856522 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people
 in different groups?
